    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">SRM Overview</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">At <text styleclass="Code Example">&gt;&gt;&gt;</text> you interact with the console using <text styleclass="Code Example">show</text> (display a variable), <text styleclass="Code Example">set</text> (change a variable), and device / diagnostic commands. Settings persist to the flash / NVRAM image. The default power-up action is HALT, so the console waits at <text styleclass="Code Example">&gt;&gt;&gt;</text> for an operator command.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">The reported console version is <text styleclass="Code Example">V7.3-2 (Feb 27 2007)</text>; <text styleclass="Code Example">PALcode is OpenVMS V1.98-83 / Tru64 UNIX V1.92-73.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
